title: House expected to vote Monday on $900 billion COVID-19 relief package with $600 stimulus checks
text: Democratic leaders in the House expect to vote Monday on a $900 billion relief package, Majority Leader Steny Hoyer said Sunday. Earlier in the day, congressional leaders announced they had reached a long-awaited deal on a COVID-19 relief package. The compromise plan includes $600 stimulus checks, a $300-a-week boost to unemployment benefits, and $300 billion in aid for small businesses via the Paycheck Protection Program.

title: Stocks give cautious welcome to U.S. aid deal, wary on Brexit
text: U.S. stock futures traded sideways in Asia on Monday as investors gave a cautious welcome to news a deal had been struck on a long-awaited U.S. stimulus bill, though "difficult" Brexit talks dragged on with no agreement in sight.

title: Dow futures edge up Sunday night as Congress strikes last-ditch, $900 billion coronavirus-aid pact
text: U.S. stock-index futures attempted to edge higher but were seeing relatively mooted gains Sunday night as Congress reached a deal on a $900 billion coronavirus relief package. Futures for the Dow Jones Industrial Average {s: ym00] rose 93 points, or 0.3%, at 30,210, those for the S&P 500 were flat at 3,707.50, while Nasdaq-100 futures rose 0.2% to reach 12,740.50.
